{"TopicId":201369,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Kerbal injury and temporary paralysis","CreatedByName":"OrdinaryKerman","CreatedById":208637,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-31T09:06:19Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"OrdinaryKerman","CreatedById":208637,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-31T09:06:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRight now, all kerbals ingame have an listed impact tolerance of 50 m/s, or 180 km/h. Any lower than that, they just walk off unharmed. Obviously, this is completely unrealistic and very silly even for a game like this. So I think Kerbals should have some sort of \u0027injuryMinSpeed\u0027 value, where impacts above this speed that don\u0027t kill a kerbal will reduce their capability. For example, they may have reduced speed when walking or climbing, may not be able to run, or be incapable of doing science. If this kind of impact occurs three times or something, the kerbal may be completely paralysed and require other kerbals to lift them back into the vessel following which they will heal after some time, perhaps as an extension of EVA construction. Sustained exposure to high G-forces could also trigger paralysis. Crashing above 50 m/s will still kill them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-03-31T13:06:01Z\u0022 title=\u002203/31/2021 01:06  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 31, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by OrdinaryKerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EAdded a G-effect\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-31T09:26:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the paralyzed part is a bit dark but I like the other ideas.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-31T09:37:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike in\u00A0 \u003Cem\u003ERobinson\u0027s Requiem\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022844b149eae3a23315774b921d440f61aa4bf4e34\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022525\u0022 width=\u0022700\u0022 src=\u0022https://static.gog.com/upload/images/2008/10/844b149eae3a23315774b921d440f61aa4bf4e34.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-31T09:58:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like it. Perhaps a \u0027medical\u0027 class of Kerbal could revive injured/incapacitated crew?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-31T10:53:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223947247\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201369\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617184713\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022160462\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022James Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n48 minutes ago, James Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI like it. Perhaps a \u0027medical\u0027 class of Kerbal could revive injured/incapacitated crew?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to see Kerbal professions expanded a little in general, actually. There could be multiple classes of engineers (eg mechanical engineers, structural engineers, electrical engineers) and scientists (eg geologists, botanists, medics), and each specialisation could have some kind of unique ability.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe this would be more suited to KSP2, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-31T11:01:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223947250\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201369\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617188007\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183830\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RealKerbal3x\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, RealKerbal3x said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe this would be more suited to KSP2, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be great to see a basic implementation in KSP and maybe an expanded version that includes benefits to crew happiness or psychology in KSP 2?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-31T12:58:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223947244\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201369\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617182769\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210116\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FruitGoose\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, FruitGoose said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the paralyzed part is a bit dark but I like the other ideas.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy thoughts exactly.\u00A0\u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003EBut Profession expansion sounds like a good thing. \u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-31T13:07:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022141813\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9804649746\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/155313-18-kerbal-health-151-2020-10-26/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:193px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe it would be better extended?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OrdinaryKerman","CreatedById":208637,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-31T13:15:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223947286\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201369\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617196037\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022141813\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1736067345\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/155313-18-kerbal-health-151-2020-10-26/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe it would be better extended?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is for kerbal impact damage, not health issues from extended stays in microgravity. But ok.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-31T13:35:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223947289\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201369\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617196523\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208637\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022OrdinaryKerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, OrdinaryKerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is for kerbal impact damage, not health issues from extended stays in microgravity. But ok.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbalism has.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022190461\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1185207804\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/190382-15-110-kerbalism-311/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:193px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nP.S.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAlso KeepFit did something like that, but is obsolete.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002297413\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8517725734\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/61510-120wip-plugin0119830102016-keepfit-kerbal-fitness-degradation/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:193px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-03-31T13:37:15Z\u0022 title=\u002203/31/2021 01:37  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 31, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OrdinaryKerman","CreatedById":208637,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-31T13:47:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223947295\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201369\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617197737\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbalism has.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022190461\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1907840344\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/190382-15-110-kerbalism-311/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nP.S.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAlso KeepFit did something like that, but is obsolete.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002297413\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6787666531\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/61510-120wip-plugin0119830102016-keepfit-kerbal-fitness-degradation/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI said this is\u00A0\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003Enot\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u00A0about long-term health, just \u0027unplanned surface braking\u0027 aka kerbals crashing into something.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dientus","CreatedById":209823,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-31T14:09:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI could see a medical professional kerbal if this were to be implemented. Which could in turn lead to more in depth play and parts such as a medical bay, and maybe even bandages for the doctor kerbal to heal other kerbals in orbit, like the engineer repairing parts and using those kits.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf done right, I could get behind and enjoy this as long as it doesn\u0027t get too dark. There are other games for that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dr. Kerbal","CreatedById":207217,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-31T16:52:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223947244\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201369\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617182769\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210116\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022FruitGoose\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, FruitGoose said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the paralyzed part is a bit dark but I like the other ideas.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe like. In the medical wing of R and D.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-03-31T17:52:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTemporarily remove experience stars ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-03T09:39:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223947309\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201369\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617199797\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022209823\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dientus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/31/2021 at 10:09 AM, Dientus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI could see a medical professional kerbal if this were to be implemented.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd the inevitable personal injury attorneys from the law firm of Kerman, Kerman, Kerman, and Kerman.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-03T09:55:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFines for violating labour safety Kerbal safety (you have to provide every Kerbal with belt, gloves, and helmet and keep under control if they are wearing them).\u003Cbr\u003E\nA sign of every \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E Kerbal before his shift in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeveral weeks to have the planned flight accepted by KAA\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022BiodegradableFlashyEel-size_restricted.g\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002257.60\u0022 height=\u0022288\u0022 width=\u0022500\u0022 src=\u0022https://thumbs.gfycat.com/BiodegradableFlashyEel-size_restricted.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Kerbal Aviation Administration) and wait for the inspector (happily, KSP doesn\u0027t have weather yet.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wpetula","CreatedById":209905,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-06T16:56:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223947240\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022201369\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221617181579\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208637\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022OrdinaryKerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/31/2021 at 5:06 AM, OrdinaryKerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor example, they may have reduced speed when walking\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs if their walking speed wasn\u0027t already snail-paced\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Single stage to ocean","CreatedById":210256,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-04-06T16:58:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u2019t like the paralysis, would prefer death/inability to jump or pilot craft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}